Questions:
What happens to your data if you choose to withdraw from the study after the follow-up period is completed?
A) Your data will be immediately destroyed and not used in the study analysis;
B) Your data will be retained and used in the study analysis, but your identifying information will be destroyed;
C) Your data and identifying information will be kept indefinitely for future research without your consent;
D) You will be required to provide a reason for your withdrawal, and your data will be kept based on that reason.

Correct answer: B

Who is authorized to inspect relevant sections of your medical notes and data collected during the study for Chronic Lymphocytic Leukaemia?
A) Only the primary researcher conducting the study;
B) Individuals from The Department for Health at the University of Bath, regulatory authorities, or the NHS Trust;
C) All staff members at the University of Bath;
D) Any member of the public interested in the research findings.

Correct answer: B

If you have any questions about your rights as a research subject or wish to discuss problems or concerns related to the study, whom should you contact?

A) The Department for Health at the University of Bath;  
B) The NHS Trust;  
C) The person who took your consent for the study;  
D) A healthcare lawyer not affiliated with the study.

Correct answer: C) The person who took your consent for the study.
